import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.metrics import r2_score
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

# Load data
train_df = pd.read_csv('data/train.csv')
test_df = pd.read_csv('data/test.csv')

# Target variable
y = train_df['SalePrice']

# Features
X = train_df.drop(['Id', 'SalePrice'], axis=1)
X_test = test_df.drop(['Id'], axis=1)

# Identify categorical and numerical columns
categorical_columns = X.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.tolist()
numerical_columns = X.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()

# Handle missing values
X[numerical_columns] = X[numerical_columns].fillna(X[numerical_columns].median())
X_test[numerical_columns] = X_test[numerical_columns].fillna(X_test[numerical_columns].median())

for col in categorical_columns:
    X[col] = X[col].fillna(X[col].mode()[0])
    X_test[col] = X_test[col].fillna(X_test[col].mode()[0])

# One-hot encode categorical variables
X_encoded = pd.get_dummies(X[categorical_columns], drop_first=True)
X_test_encoded = pd.get_dummies(X_test[categorical_columns], drop_first=True)

# Align columns by ensuring identical feature names
X_final = pd.concat([X[numerical_columns], X_encoded], axis=1)
X_test_final = pd.concat([X_test[numerical_columns], X_test_encoded], axis=1)

# Make sure both datasets have exactly the same columns (by reindexing)
X_final = X_final.reindex(columns=X_final.columns.tolist())
X_test_final = X_test_final.reindex(columns=X_final.columns.tolist())

# Split train data
X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(X_final, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Train model
model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, max_depth=10, random_state=42)
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Validate
y_pred_val = model.predict(X_val)
val_r2 = r2_score(y_val, y_pred_val)
print(f"Validation R²: {val_r2}")

# Predict on test s
